issue.title: NullPointerException causes server crash when moving towards a quantum bridge
issue.body:
### Describe the bug

When approaching one quantum bridge on the nether ceiling our server crashes.
It occurs repeatedly at roughly the same location when a player moves towards it, probably when the player is near enough that the region with the quantum bridge is getting loaded.

The server always crashes with the same exception and very similar stacktrace, indicating a NullPointer here: https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/blob/master/src/main/java/appeng/me/cluster/implementations/QuantumCluster.java#L233

After the server restarted the player can continue to walk towards the Quantum bridge which also works as expected then.

### How to reproduce the bug

I haven't figured that out yet unfortunately and would like to kindly ask if you have an idea how this exception may occur.

### Expected behavior

No server crash

### Additional details

_No response_

### Which minecraft version are you using?

1.20

### On which mod loaders does it happen?

Fabric

### Crash log

https://gist.github.com/1bd1b/bae690c433196559ff1e182ea34721d0

issue.title: Sculk Transmitter from Deeper and Darker crashes game when placed into ME storage
issue.body:
### Describe the bug

A Sculk transmitter from the mod Deeper and Darker was placed into the ME storage system. This transmitter was also linked to a barrel in the overworld. Upon accessing the crafting terminal, searching for the sculk transmitter item caused the game to crash. 

### How to reproduce the bug

1. Link sculk transmitter to barrel.
2. Place sculk transmitter in ME storage.
3. Destroy barrel.
4. Search for sculk transmitter in ME storage and hover over item.

### Expected behavior

The sculk transmitter item renders properly, and can be placed and removed from the storage system as normal.

### Additional details

_No response_

### Which minecraft version are you using?

1.20

### On which mod loaders does it happen?

Forge

### Crash log

https://pastebin.com/SLN7CvyZ

comment.body:
seems like the deepderdark mod does not like their blocks to be moved
can the transmitter even be moved by a piston without crashing?! 
you should ask deeperdarker dev about this issue and put the block on the blacklist for teleporting in the mean while to avoid that happening again

issue.title: [1.20.1] Spatial IO does nothing when given redstone signal (error in server console)
issue.body:
### Describe the bug

When trying to activate a spatial io port, it does nothing, but it provides an error in the server console https://mclo.gs/50Z3Ihx

### How to reproduce the bug

Build a spatial setup of any size (in this case, enough for a 1x1x1), put a spatial drive into the spatial io port, and press the button on it, and it does nothing and gives a error in console.

### Expected behavior

It should take the block, and store it in the spatial drive

### Additional details

Using Neoforge 47.1.79 (latest), in a modpack with around 100 other mods (can provide a list if thats the suspected issue)
Also running on a server, not singleplayer.

### Which minecraft version are you using?

1.20

### On which mod loaders does it happen?

Forge

### Crash log

https://mclo.gs/50Z3Ihx

comment.body:
[Just uploaded a version](https://modrinth.com/mod/biome-makeover/version/forge-1.20.1-1.11.2) that use's it's own namespace.

Thanks for making me aware - give me a shout if there's any further issues!

issue.title: Quantum Bridge across chunk border cause a "Too many chained neighbor updates" error.
issue.body:
### Describe the bug

![image](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/46108547/baf145aa-f688-4bfc-a609-a7c18da14cac)
Quantum Bridge across chunk border cause a "Too many chained neighbor updates" error.
```
[04:08:56] [Server thread/ERROR]: Too many chained neighbor updates. Skipping the rest. First skipped position: 992, 75, 2003
```
At the position of a Quantum Ring.

### How to reproduce the bug

1. Build a Quantum Bridge at spawn chunks.
![image](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/46108547/3d8bdf6f-f4b3-423a-a1d0-5a31ca193188)
2. Build another Quantum Bridge at a border of non-spawn chunks, as shown in the picture. connect each other with Quantum Entangled Singularity.
![image](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/46108547/c095990e-8ae6-442e-90aa-641f0dfe6d17)
3. Place a Fluix Cable as shown in the picture. I this case, place on the east side.
![image](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/46108547/82db07eb-fd28-4be0-a525-b266b52a38c9)
4. Fly far away until the chunk of Quantum Bridge unloaded. In this case, fly to east.
5. Fly back. The chunk loading stucked. The game prints a "Too many chained neighbor updates" error in the log.

### Expected behavior

The "Too many chained neighbor updates" error should not happen.

### Additional details

The crash report is generated by holding F3+C.

### Which minecraft version are you using?

1.20

### On which mod loaders does it happen?

Fabric

### Crash log

https://gist.github.com/Harveykang/87aafe18bbc582cec83b3c89ab0e52c8

![2023-10-21_10 34 01](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/1788847/187c6972-607e-4cc6-a4c6-d11c8dc14245)

issue.body:
### Describe the bug

![image](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/46108547/baf145aa-f688-4bfc-a609-a7c18da14cac)
Quantum Bridge across chunk border cause a "Too many chained neighbor updates" error.
```
[04:08:56] [Server thread/ERROR]: Too many chained neighbor updates. Skipping the rest. First skipped position: 992, 75, 2003
```
At the position of a Quantum Ring.

### How to reproduce the bug

1. Build a Quantum Bridge at spawn chunks.
![image](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/46108547/3d8bdf6f-f4b3-423a-a1d0-5a31ca193188)
2. Build another Quantum Bridge at a border of non-spawn chunks, as shown in the picture. connect each other with Quantum Entangled Singularity.
![image](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/46108547/c095990e-8ae6-442e-90aa-641f0dfe6d17)
3. Place a Fluix Cable as shown in the picture. I this case, place on the east side.
![image](https://github.com/AppliedEnergistics/Applied-Energistics-2/assets/46108547/82db07eb-fd28-4be0-a525-b266b52a38c9)
4. Fly far away until the chunk of Quantum Bridge unloaded. In this case, fly to east.
5. Fly back. The chunk loading stucked. The game prints a "Too many chained neighbor updates" error in the log.

### Expected behavior

The "Too many chained neighbor updates" error should not happen.

### Additional details

The crash report is generated by holding F3+C.

### Which minecraft version are you using?

1.20

### On which mod loaders does it happen?

Fabric

### Crash log

https://gist.github.com/Harveykang/87aafe18bbc582cec83b3c89ab0e52c8

issue.title: Numerous crash issues with AE2 and seemingly REI parity. Fabric 1.18.2
issue.body:
### Describe the bug

For the past few days while I've been using AE2, I've been in a few situations when interacting with REI that I experience a game crash.

In every case, it gives the following crash error, and stacktrace.

```
java.lang.IllegalStateException: Pose stack not empty
	at net.minecraft.class_761.method_22979(class_761.java:1553)
	at net.minecraft.class_761.method_22710(class_761.java:1369)
	at net.minecraft.class_757.method_3188(class_757.java:1034)
	at net.minecraft.class_757.method_3192(class_757.java:813)
	at net.minecraft.class_310.method_1523(class_310.java:1122)
	at net.minecraft.class_310.method_1514(class_310.java:737)
	at net.minecraft.client.main.Main.main(Main.java:236)
	at net.fabricmc.loader.impl.game.minecraft.MinecraftGameProvider.launch(MinecraftGameProvider.java:468)
	at net.fabricmc.loader.impl.launch.knot.Knot.launch(Knot.java:74)
	at net.fabricmc.loader.impl.launch.knot.KnotClient.main(KnotClient.java:23)
	at org.prismlauncher.launcher.impl.StandardLauncher.launch(StandardLauncher.java:88)
	at org.prismlauncher.EntryPoint.listen(EntryPoint.java:126)
	at org.prismlauncher.EntryPoint.main(EntryPoint.java:71)
```
```
Stacktrace:
	at net.minecraft.class_761.method_22979(class_761.java:1553)
	at net.minecraft.class_761.method_22710(class_761.java:1369)
	at net.minecraft.class_757.method_3188(class_757.java:1034)
```

### How to reproduce the bug

Situations where this crash has occurred:
- REI Quick-Crafting (Ctrl+Click) a Charger, ME Interface, Energy Cell, or Inscriber
- Typing letters while in the middle of a search (inconsistent)
- Shift Clicking Storage Cells in and out of an ME IO Port (inconsistent)

Situations where this crash has **NOT** occurred:
- Opening up AE2 Machines / UIs
- REI Quick-Crafting (Ctrl+Click) Annihilation Cores, Formation Cores, Illumination Panels, Item Storage Components, or Quartz Glass 


Note: For crash cases, the game does save the last position items were in. For example if you have Visual Workbench installed, then a quick-craft crash at a crafting table would have the items you quick-crafted in the workbench when you reload the world. Same goes for the ME Crafting Interface.
No data seems to be lost from these crashes, for now at least.

### Expected behavior

The expected behavior is whatever action going on occurs without a crash.

### Additional details

_No response_

### Which minecraft version are you using?

1.18

### On which mod loaders does it happen?

Fabric

### Crash log

https://paste.ee/p/9Rhkd (this has both the crash & latest.log attached)

comment.body:
Big Update: Conflict is specifically the mod "Roughly Searchable". If the functionality of this mod is disabled, then the crash does not happen.
https://legacy.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/roughly-searchable
